<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jerry Lewis Stalker Release </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- A man who spent more than four years in prison  
for stalking entertainer Jerry Lewis has been released. 
</P>
<P>
	Gary Benson, a 56-year-old diagnosed chronic schizophrenic, was  
released Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	He was convicted in 1995 of aggravated stalking and sentenced to  
six years in prison. He received time off with work credits and 
good behavior, state prison spokesman Howard Skolnik said. 
</P>
<P>
	Benson, who said he is moving out of state to start a new life,  
on Wednesday told the television show ``Extra'' that he never 
threatened Lewis. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think in a sense I was stalking him,'' he said. ``I  
made several calls to his house and I've been to his house to meet 
with him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Justice of the Peace Jennifer Togliatti last week granted Lewis'  
request to extend a 1992 protection order against Benson until 
Sept. 21, 2000. Lewis has said he and his family lived in fear of 
Benson. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
