<HEADLINE> Freezer-Bodies Suspect Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- A man who eluded authorities for more than a  
week after police found the bodies of his wife and infant son in a 
freezer was arrested early Thursday nearly 500 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
	John K. Adams, 24, was arrested near Kansas City, Mo., after a  
police officer found him sleeping in a rented van with a license 
plate stolen in Illinois. A gun was found in the van. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams had not been seen since Sept. 21, the day before a deputy  
found the frozen bodies of Robin Schafer-Adams, 24, and the 
couple's infant son, John R. Adams. 
</P>
<P>
	The woman had been shot to death, and the child, who would have  
been 10 months old, had been strangled, authorities said. The 
bodies may have been in the freezer for up to three months. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams had not been charged in connection with the deaths, but he  
is wanted in Indianapolis in connection with holdups at two Pizza 
Hut restaurants. Adams is a former Pizza Hut delivery man. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies were found by a deputy coming to serve Adams with a  
robbery arrest warrant. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
