<HEADLINE> Elderly Man Charged in Cane Killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- An elderly man wielding a cane bludgeoned a  
51-year-old woman to death outside a nightclub after she insulted 
his wife, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Walter Lee Kuykendall, 71, was charged Wednesday with  
second-degree manslaughter in the death of Royce Harris. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the attack occurred July 13 as Kuykendall, Ms.  
Harris and several friends gathered behind the Players Club. 
Witnesses told police Kuykendall became angry and struck Ms. Harris 
in the head with his cane after she made offensive comments about 
his wife. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Harris died the next day.  
</P>
<P>
	Kuykendall is free on $10,000 bond. He faces two to 20 years in  
prison if convicted. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
