<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 16:20:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Teen Gets Life in Torture Slaying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROCKVILLE, Md. (AP) -- A 16-year-old boy was sentenced to life in  
prison Thursday for masterminding a plot that led to the brutal 
beating, torture and death of a 15-year-old. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirill Varnovatyy was bludgeoned and stabbed 27 times before  
Aaron Goldfarb slashed his throat with a switchblade knife taken 
from the victim, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	``The torture and terror that Mr. Varnovatyy experienced is  
unimaginable,'' Maryland Circuit Court Judge Nelson W. Rupp Jr. 
said 
</P>
<P>
	On Sept. 7, 1998, Varnovatyy thought he was going to Quince  
Orchard Valley Park in Gaithersburg, Md., to smoke cigarettes and 
drink beer, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Court records indicate he pleaded for his life during a series  
of attacks on several isolated acres of parkland. 
</P>
<P>
	``He went out with people that he thought were his friends and  
they killed him,'' prosecutor Katherine Winfree said. 
</P>
<P>
	She said Goldfarb blamed Varnovatyy for arranging a deal for  
phony drugs. 
</P>
<P>
	Joseph Philip Morrongiello, 20, and Zachary Smith Marshall, 16,  
both pleaded guilty to second-degree murder in the case. They are 
to be sentenced in November. 
</P>
<P>
	Although Morrongiello and Marshall admitted beating Varnovatyy,  
prosecutors say it was Goldfarb who wielded the knife that severed 
his victim's carotid artery and jugular vein, and perforated his 
trachea. 
</P>
<P>
	Goldfarb pleaded guilty to first-degree murder in June. Because  
he was 15 at the time of the crime, he was ineligible for the death 
penalty. Prosecutors said Goldfarb could be eligible for parole in 
25 years with the governor's consent. 
</P>
<P>
	``He is not a monster, he is the boy next door,'' Cheryl  
Etchison said in a tearful plea for leniency for her son. 
</P>
<P>
	Goldfarb allegedly was the victim of sexual abuse that began  
when he was 5. A psychiatrist testified that Goldfarb also suffers 
from drug and alcohol abuse and depression. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
