<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Money Funds Fall in Latest Week / Money Market Funds  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Assets of the nation's retail money market  
mutual funds fell by $3.64 billion in the latest week to $895.20 
billion, the Investment Company Institute said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of taxable money market funds in the retail category fell  
by $2.01 billion to $746.60 billion for the week ended Wednesday, 
the Washington-based mutual fund trade group said. Tax-exempt fund 
assets fell by $1.63 billion to $148.60 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Assets of institutional money market funds fell by $5.20 billion  
to $600.62 billion for the same period. Among institutional funds, 
taxable money market fund assets fell by $4.92 billion to $554.36 
billion; assets of tax-exempt funds fell by $273.4 million to 
$46.27 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Total money market assets stood at $1.496 trillion for the week.  
</P>
<P>
	Assets for the previous week were revised to $1.505 trillion to  
reflect reporting errors and a change in the number of funds 
reporting. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day average yield on money market mutual funds rose in  
the week ended Tuesday to 4.71 percent from 4.69 percent the 
previous week, said IBC's Money Fund Report, a trade journal 
published in Ashland, Mass., by IBC Financial Data Inc. The 30-day 
average yield rose to 4.69 percent from 4.66 percent, IBC Financial 
Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-day compounded yield rose to 4.82 percent from 4.80  
percent the previous week, and the 30-day compounded yield rose to 
4.80 percent from 4.77 percent, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was  
57 days, unchanged from a week earlier, IBC Financial Data said. 
</P>
<P>
	The online service bankrate.com said its survey of 100 leading  
commercial banks, savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nation's 10 largest markets showed the annual percentage 
yield available on money market accounts was 2.08 percent as of 
Wednesday unchanged from a week earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	The North Palm Beach, Fla.-based unit of Intelligent Life Corp.  
said the annual percentage yield available on interest-bearing 
checking accounts held steady at 0.84 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Bankrate.com said the annual percentage yield was 4.37 percent  
on six-month certificates of deposit, up from 4.35 percent the 
previous week. Yields were 4.74 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 4.73 
percent; 5.02 percent on 2 1/2-year CDs, up from 5.01 percent; and 
5.25 percent on 5-year CDs, unchanged from a week earlier. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
