<HEADLINE> Islanders Sign Top Pick Connolly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- The New York Islanders rewarded center  
Tim Connolly and defenseman Mathieu Biron for making the parent 
club by signing them to three-year deals Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Connolly was the first of the Islanders' four first-round picks  
in this year's Entry Draft and the fifth overall. The Kings made 
Biron the 21st choice in the first round. The choice was acquired 
from Los Angeles as part of the trade for Zigmund Palffy on June 
