<DOCNO> APW19990930.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 05:50:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Swissair Won't Carry the Deported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) -- Swissair will no longer carry  
passengers who are being deported forcibly from Switzerland, the 
company said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Swiss national carrier's decision came into force Sept. 10,  
spokesman Urs Peter Naef said. 
</P>
<P>
	Incidents involving people resisting deportation have caused  
increasing problems with passengers and flight crews, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	In one such case in May, a Congolese man escaped deportation  
after fellow passengers on a Swissair flight to Kinshasa attacked 
his three police guards during a stopover in Cameroon. 
</P>
<P>
	The Swiss officers returned to Switzerland because local  
authorities wouldn't let the plane continue unless the detainee was 
taken back. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
