<HEADLINE> Compaq Names Human Resources Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Compaq Computer Corp. has named a former Burger  
King Corp. executive as its new senior vice president for human 
resources. 
</P>
<P>
	Yvonne Jackson is the first senior executive hired by Michael  
Capellas, who was named Compaq's chief executive in July. She will 
begin her new job on Nov. 8. 
</P>
<P>
	As Burger King's senior vice president of worldwide human  
resources, Ms. Jackson supervised a work force of about 25,000 
people, less than half the size of Compaq's. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining Burger King in 1993, she spent 13 years in human  
resources management at Avon Products. She began her career at 
Sears, Roebuck and Co. 
</P>
<P>
	``Yvonne's experience with customer-focused companies like  
Burger King, Avon and Sears will be a tremendous asset as we work 
to make customer advocacy an important part of Compaq's culture,'' 
Capellas said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson's top priority will be completing integration of Digital  
Equipment Corp., which Houston-based Compaq bought last year, and 
Tandem Computers, which it acquired in 1997. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
