<HEADLINE> Highway Named After Gene Autry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A freeway interchange was named to honor Gene  
Autry on what would have been the singing cowboy's 92nd birthday. 
</P>
<P>
	As a children's choir sang Autry's signature ``Back in the  
Saddle Again,'' his widow, Jackie Autry, pulled a cord Wednesday to 
unveil a green-and-white sign stating ``Gene Autry Memorial 
Interchange.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The interchange of Interstate 5 and the 134 Freeway provides  
motorists with access to the Autry Museum of Western Heritage. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think that he really personified the romance of the old West  
and it was not only that he was a fine actor and musician, he had 
such a strength of character,'' said state Sen. Adam Schiff, who 
sponsored the legislation to name the interchange. 
</P>
<P>
	Autry, who played a cowboy in movies and TV, also owned major  
league baseball's Anaheim Angels franchise and broadcast stations. 
He died last year. 
  	   	
</P>
