<HEADLINE> SFX Buys Out Agent Art Tellem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- SFX Entertainment Inc. bought out agent Arn  
Tellem on Wednesday, adding Albert Belle and Nomar Garciaparra to a 
client group that already includes Roger Clemens, Patrick Ewing, 
Alonzo Mourning, Hakeem Olajuwon. 
</P>
<P>
	SFX last year bought out agent David Falk for about $80 million  
plus what is now 2 million shares of stock, which is worth about 
$66 million if he still has it. With that deal, it acquired a group 
of players that included Michael Jordan. 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this year, SFX bought the sports business of agents Alan  
and Randy Hendricks, whose clients include Chuck Knoblauch, Ben 
Grieve, Ryan Klesko, Al Leiter and Kerry Wood, for $15.7 million, 
$5 million in deferred payments plus the chance to earn additional 
bonuses. 
</P>
<P>
	With Wednesday's deal to acquire Tellem &AMP; Associates, SFX  
acquires a client list of about 20 major league baseball players 
and 35 NBA players. The price of the Tellem deal was not 
immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
	SFX also owns or operates, partially or entirely, 116 venues  
including 16 amphitheaters. 



  	   	
</P>
