<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Safeway Inc., down 4 11/16 at 38 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The grocery chain reported third-quarter earnings of 44 cents  
per share, in line with analysts' expectations and above last 
year's third-quarter profits of 38 cents per share. The company 
said comparable-store sales rose 1 percent in the quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Aetna Inc., down 10 7/16 at 49 1/4  
</P>
<P>
 *United HealthCare Corp., down 11 13/16 at 48 11/16 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of most health insurers fell after the Wall Street  
Journal reported trial lawyers may soon file class-action lawsuits 
on behalf of managed-care patients. Such lawsuits would hurt the 
companies' ability to control costs. 

</P>
<P>
 *Guidant Corp., up 3 15/16 at 53 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Merrill Lynch named Guidant, a maker of cardiology products, its  
top pick in the medical technology sector. Merrill cited the 
company's ``long-term sustainable revenue growth'' and potential 
new cardiology products. 

</P>
<P>
 *AutoZone Inc., up 2 3/4 at 28 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, an auto parts maker, earned 67 cents per share in  
its fiscal fourth quarter, up from 60 cents per share in the fourth 
quarter of 1998. AutoZone said same-store sales rose 2 percent in 
the quarter. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Flycast Communications Corp., up 7 1/2 at 45 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	CMGI Inc. will acquire Flycast, a provider of Web-based direct  
advertising Communications Corp., for about $690 million in stock. 
CMGI invests in and develops Internet-related businesses. 

</P>
<P>
 *TiVo Inc., priced at 16, trading 29 15/16 at 29 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The maker of personalized television systems soared in its  
initial public offering. TiVo shares were expected to be priced at 
11 to 13 per share. The company began selling its systems in March, 
and had revenue of $8,000 in the first six months of 1999. 

</P>
<P>
 *InterNAP Networks Services Corp., down 8 23/64 at 44 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Investors took some profits following InterNAP's strong initial  
public offering Wednesday. Shares were priced at 20 and closed at 
52 63/64, continuing a trend of strong showings from Internet 
infrastructure companies. 

</P>
<P>
 *US Xpress Enterprises Inc., down 3 3/16 at 5 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The transportation company said third-quarter revenues will miss  
expectations due to a shortfall in tractor additions and lower than 
expected equipment utilization. US Xpress said it has been 
adversely affected by increasing fuel costs. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
