<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> John Lennon Lyric Sheet Sold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Sold! Goo goo ga joob.  
</P>
<P>
	The lyrics for John Lennon's ``I Am the Walrus'' sold for  
$129,000 in an auction at Christie's on Thursday. The lyric sheet 
contains 20 lines of the 1967 Beatles classic and was sold to an 
anonymous telephone bidder. 
</P>
<P>
	The sheet contains Lennon's notes and changes, including the  
deletion of the word ``policeman,'' which was changed to 
``priestess.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The lyrics are believed to have been inspired by the Lewis  
Carroll poem ``The Walrus and the Carpenter.'' 
</P>
<P>
	George Harrison's 1962 Rickenbacker guitar also went to an  
anonymous bidder for $92,900. 
</P>
<P>
	Other top sellers included an Elvis Presley shirt, worn in the  
1970 movie ``Elvis -- That's the Way It Is.'' It went for nearly 
$32,900. Presley's cream-colored stage suit sold for $20,800. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
