<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan, German Banks in Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's Sakura Bank Ltd. has formed an alliance  
with Germany's Deutsche Bank AG for bond and stock underwriting 
starting in October. 
</P>
<P>
	Sakura Securities Co. and the Tokyo branch of Deutsche  
Securities Ltd. will cooperate in marketing for Japanese clients 
issuing bonds and stocks in Japan and overseas, and for overseas 
companies issuing securities in Japan, the banks announced 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The alliance will enable Sakura Securities to use the Deutsche  
Bank group's strong product development capability and global 
network. 
</P>
<P>
	The German financial group, which already has several business  
arrangements with Japanese institutions, will get access to 
Sakura's corporate customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Sakura Bank also said Thursday that its asset management unit  
will cooperate with three foreign asset management companies in 
U.S., European and global stock investment management. 
</P>
<P>
	The three foreign institutions are Alliance Capital Management  
LP of New York, State Street of Boston and Deutsche Asset 
Management of Germany. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
