<HEADLINE> German Wins Nobel in Literature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) -- Guenter Grass of Germany won the 1999  
Nobel Prize in literature today. 
</P>
<P>
	The Swedish Academy cited Grass' first novel, ``The Tin Drum,''  
published in 1959. ``Here he comes to grips with the enormous task 
of reviewing contemporary history by recalling the disavowed and 
the forgotten: the victims, losers and lies that people wanted to 
forget because they had once believed in them.... 
</P>
<P>
	``It is not too audacious to assume that ``The Tin Drum'' will  
become one of the enduring literary works of the 20th century.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
