<HEADLINE> Fleet-BankBoston Merger Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Massachusetts regulators approved Fleet Financial  
Group's takeover of BankBoston on Thursday, removing the final 
obstacle to the creation of New England's largest bank and the 
eighth biggest in the country. 
</P>
<P>
	The two companies plan to file documents Friday with state  
regulators that will seal the deal, which already has been cleared 
by federal regulators, is now expected to close on Friday, the 
companies said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Massachusetts Board of Bank Incorporation voted 3-0 to  
approve the $16 billion takeover. 
</P>
<P>
	Fleet, currently the nation's ninth-largest bank, has $69.7  
billion in deposits and $104.4 billion in assets. No. 15 BankBoston 
has $48.5 billion in deposits and $73.5 billion in assets. 
</P>
<P>
	Federal regulators had required that Fleet and BankBoston sell  
off 306 branches to ensure the new company wouldn't dominate the 
market. On Thursday, the banks announced they would sell off an 
additional seven branches in Connecticut to satisfy state 
regulators. 
</P>
<P>
	The companies also pledged to lend $14.6 billion over the next  
five years in affordable mortgages, small business loans and other 
programs for low- to moderate-income people. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
