<HEADLINE> Stolen Camera Shows Attack Evidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- A man who allegedly videotaped himself wearing  
a diaper and molesting a 4-year-old girl was arrested after his 
camcorder was stolen and re-sold with the tape still inside. 
</P>
<P>
	William Hampton, 44, was charged with sodomy and using a child  
for a sexual performance. Hampton, who's being held on $200,000 
bail, also faces a federal count of producing child pornography. 
</P>
<P>
	Police say the 15-minute tape was found in the camera stolen  
from Hampton's St. Louis home earlier this month. The camera's 
buyer contacted police, and it was linked to a 17-year-old burglar 
whose mother had sold it for $150. 
</P>
<P>
	The thief, whose name wasn't released, was arrested Sept. 22 on  
unrelated burglary charges. He told police he stole the camcorder 
about a week before his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
	Lt. Mary Warnecke, commander of the St. Louis Police  
Department's sex crimes and child abuse unit, said the girl on the 
tape is the daughter of one of Hampton's former girlfriends. 
Hampton had custody of the girl one day a week for more than a 
year, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We believe his role was to be a fatherly figure to the girl,''  
Warnecke said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said the tape apparently was made in Hampton's  
home within the past few months. 
</P>
<P>
	The girl remains in her mother's care and is expected to receive  
counseling. Police said the mother had been unaware of the sex acts 
or the taping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
