<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NY Gallery Owner Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Bullets as party favors? It was part of an art  
gallery show, but police say it was illegal. 
</P>
<P>
	Mary Boone, owner of the Mary Boone Gallery, was arrested  
Wednesday on charges of illegal distribution of ammunition, said 
police Sgt. Ellen Tietjen. Police allegedly found a vase filled 
with 100 rounds of 9 mm bullets. 
</P>
<P>
	Visitors to the Fifth Avenue gallery were reportedly invited to  
help themselves to cartridges and take them home. 
</P>
<P>
	``If this were simply someone handing bullets out on the street,  
you would criticize us greatly for not doing something about it,'' 
said police spokeswoman Marilyn Mode. ``This is an unsupervised 
exhibit with a glass vase filled with bullets, live ammunition.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The one-man show of sculptor Tom Sachs featured homemade guns --  
his signature object. Sachs' work deals with consumer culture, 
packaging and violence. 
</P>
<P>
	When the guns were deemed functional, criminal possession of a  
weapon and criminal possession of a shotgun were added to the 
charges, Mode said. 
</P>
<P>
	Misdemeanor charges carry a maximum penalty of a year in jail,  
plus fines. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
