<HEADLINE> Geraldo Rivera, Wife Separating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIDDLETOWN, N.J. (AP) -- Geraldo Rivera and his fourth wife are  
separating after 12 years of marriage, a spokesman for the talk 
show host said. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple on Monday confirmed they have been living apart.  
</P>
<P>
	Rivera and C.C. Dyer are working together amicably toward a  
legal separation and there are no current plans for a divorce, 
according to a statement issued by Rivera's public relations firm 
Wednesday 
</P>
<P>
	The two have lived together for 19 years and have two daughters,  
ages 6 and 5. 
</P>
<P>
	The two also plan to continue working together on civic  
activities. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Dyer is publisher of The Two River Times, a weekly newspaper  
in Monmouth County. Rivera has a talk show on cable channel CNBC. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
