<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Open Higher / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones  
Industrial Average is up 38 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold decliners of almost 
2-1. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 4 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up 4 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Analysts expected stocks to move higher after the second quarter  
gross domestic product numbers indicated a possible reason for the 
Fed to leave interest rates where they are. 
</P>
<P>
	The economy posted its slowest growth in four years.  
</P>
<P>
	The Commerce Department says the gross domestic product grew at  
an annual rate of 1.6 percent. That's down slightly from previous 
government estimates. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's session could be marked by continued volatility.  
</P>
<P>
	It is the end of the quarter and the markets are subject to some  
window dressing as managers add and subtract stocks to make their 
portfolios look as good as possible. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
