<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> College Football Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Bring on the Heisman candidates. Michigan welcomes the  
challenge. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, the Wolverines held Wisconsin running back Ron Dayne  
to 88 yards -- none in the second half -- in beating the Badgers. Now 
they get a shot at Purdue quarterback Drew Brees. 
</P>
<P>
	No. 4 Michigan's matchup with No. 11 Purdue is one of the  
highlights of Saturday's college football schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Saturday, No. 1 Florida State plays at Duke, No. 3 Florida  
is home against No. 21 Alabama, No. 5 Texas A&AMP;M at Texas Tech, No. 
6 Nebraska meets Oklahoma State, No. 7 Tennessee plays Auburn, No. 
8 Virginia Tech is at No. 24 Virginia, and No. 10 Georgia plays 
LSU. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition, No. 12 Ohio State meets Wisconsin, No. 13 Kansas  
State is at No. 15 Texas, No. 14 Michigan State plays Iowa, No. 16 
Mississippi State visits Vanderbilt, No. 17 Marshall is at Miami, 
Ohio, No. 19 East Carolina meets Army, No. 20 Arkansas is at 
Kentucky, No. 22 Syracuse plays Tulane, No. 23 Oklahoma is at Notre 
Dame, and No. 25 Oregon is at Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	The weekend began Thursday night with No. 9 Georgia Tech at home  
against Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
	Two teams -- No. 2 Penn State and No. 18 Miami -- are idle.  
</P>
<P>
	After stalling Dayne's run at Ricky Williams' NCAA rushing  
record, Michigan's pass defense gets tested against Brees, who has 
completed 107 of 172 passes for 1,315 yards and 10 TDs, and is 
fourth nationally in total offense at 343.2 yards per game. 
</P>
<P>
	He threw for 405 yards and three touchdowns -- one a  
school-record 99-yarder -- in last week's 31-23 win over 
Northwestern. That victory extended Purdue's winning streak to 10 
games, longest in the nation and longest for the Boilermakers since 
winning 11 straight from 1928-30. 
</P>
<P>
	Brees decided the performance was ``so-so.'' That's because he  
brings a perfectionist approach to his job. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think I should complete every pass, unless I'm trying to  
throw the ball away to avoid a sack,'' he said. ``Having that goal 
makes me a better player.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Joe Tiller understands.  
</P>
<P>
	``Sometimes he has a tendency to be a little too hard on  
himself,'' he said. ``He's a very competitive person and he wants 
to be right every time. He actually does believe he can play a 
perfect game and complete every pass. I appreciate that. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's tough on himself right after a game. What's good about  
him is he forgets quickly and gets on to the next game.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Michigan has a double-barrel quarterback situation with Tom  
Brady and Drew Henson sharing the work. So far, it's worked for the 
Wolverines, who, like Purdue, are 4-0 and 1-0 in the Big Ten. 
</P>
<P>
	Florida hasn't lost at home since 1994 and its early season  
victory over defending champion Tennessee is testimony to the 
strength of the Gators. None of that scares Alabama defensive end 
Kenny Smith, who boldly predicted a victory for the Crimson Tide in 
The Swamp Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's up to us to have a good game and break that streak,''  
Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
	If they do, Shaun Alexander will have to be on top of his game.  
</P>
<P>
	With Dayne's Heisman credentials put in doubt by Michigan, and  
Texas Tech's Ricky Williams finished for the season because of a 
sprained knee, Alexander might be the nation's best running back. 
He has scored 10 of the Tide's 17 touchdowns this season and is 624 
yards away from the school rushing record. 
</P>
<P>
	Tennessee is struggling at 2-1 after managing only 10 first  
downs and 216 yards of offense in a 17-16 victory over Memphis. 
There also are academic allegations hanging over the Volunteers, 
and co-captain and cornerback Dwayne Goodrich was suspended after 
being arrested for disorderly conduct last weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Still, they'll get no sympathy from Auburn, down to third-string  
quarterback Jerry Klein after Ben Leard separated a shoulder and 
Gabe Gross decided to concentrate on baseball. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
