<DOCNO> APW19990930.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 05:20:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Falls, Gold Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar fell today against most major  
currencies in European trading. Gold prices were mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0688, up from $1.0615 Wednesday.  
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates compared with late Wednesday included 105.42  
Japanese yen, down from 106.78; 1.4932 Swiss francs, down from 
1.5066, and 1.4655 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4634. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6468, up from $1.6422.  
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8299 German marks, down from 1.8430; 
6.1373 French francs, down from 6.1813; 2.0619 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0770, and 1,811.63 Italian lire, down from 1,824.95. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold dealers in London fixed a recommended price of $303.75 bid  
per troy ounce at midmorning, up from $301.00 on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid was $299.50, down from $305.60.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $8.50 in Hong Kong to close at $300.50.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver opened in London at $5.55 per troy ounce, down from  
$5.65. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
