<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0648 in late European trading, up from  
$1.0615 Wednesday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro 
traded at $1.0624. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Wednesday,  
included 106.44 Japanese yen, down from 106.78; 1.5008 Swiss 
francs, down from 1.5066; 1.4690 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4634. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6462 up from $1.6422.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 106.73 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6458. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8368 German marks, down from 1.8430; 
6.1621 French francs, down from 6.1813; 2.0702 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0770l;1,818.95 Italian lire, down from 1,824.95. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $300.50 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$301.00 on Wednesday. In Zurich the bid price was $298.20, down 
from $305.60 Gold fell $8.50 in Hong Kong to $300.50 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.58 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.65 
  	   	
