<DOCNO> APW19990930.0365 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-30 17:30:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Milwaukee Gets 2002 All-Star Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Miller Park, whose opening was pushed back a  
year until 2001, will be the site of baseball's All-Star game the 
following season. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement had been expected since Bud Selig, whose family  
controls the Brewers through a trust, became commissioner in July 
1998. The All-Star game was last at Milwaukee in 1975 and orginally 
was scheduled to return this year. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's an opportunity for us to show off nationally -- to show  
off internationally -- both Miller Park and all the things going on 
in this community,'' said Brewers president Wendy Selig-Prieb, the 
commissioner's daughter. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brewers had hoped to move from County Stadium to adjacent  
Miller Park next season, but a construction accident in July killed 
three ironworkers and delayed the ballpark's completion a full 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Brewers headed for a seventh consecutive losing season,  
manager Phil Garner was fired mid-season and general manager Sal 
Bando was reassigned. 
</P>
<P>
	Selig-Prieb called the announcement about the 2002 All-Star game  
and last week's hiring of new general manager Dean Taylor ``the 
beginning of what I hoped would be a lot of good news.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Selig said Milwaukee can expect to see at least 100,000 visitors  
in town for the game. The game could be worth $70 to $80 million to 
the city's economy, Selig said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brewers originally were awarded the 1999 All-Star game. Then  
it became Miller Park wouldn't be ready this year, and the Brewers 
then switched to the National League. 
</P>
<P>
	This year's game is in Boston. The All-Star game will be at  
Atlanta next season and at Seattle in 2001. 
</P>
<P>
	The only time the Brewers have been host to an All Star game was  
for the NL's 6-3 win in 1975. The game also was played in Milwaukee 
in 1955, when the Braves were located in the city. The NL won 6-5. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
